The following companies had unusual
price changes in Argentine trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as of the close of trading. The
 Merval (MERVAL)  index rose 0.8 percent to 2,403.60.  Pampa Energia SA (PAMP)   rose 0.9 percent to 1.15 pesos
after falling as much as 0.9 percent earlier in the day. The
company announced yesterday that Central Termica Loma de la Lata
SA, an Argentine electricity generator owned by Pampa Energia,
will buy back as much as $25 million of outstanding 2015 notes.  YPF SA (YPFD)  , Argentinaâ€™s state-run oil company, was
unchaged at 85 pesos after earlier losing 2 percent. The company
held today its first shareholder meeting since the government
took control of the company in April.  To contact the reporter on this story:
